cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the impact of DDoS attacks on victim firms, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The analysis also involves the use of on-line tools and event studies, which could be related to cybercrime (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). The impact on customer services could be related to social and information networks (cs.SI) and the interruption of services could be related to computer engineering (cs.CE).
